Plug-in name: ACSL importer
Plug-in shortname: acsl-import
Description: external ACSL files importer

Most options of the form '-acsl-import-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-acsl-import-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-acsl-import <f1,...,fn>  ACSL files to import (preferably use
                    -acsl-import="f1,...,fn")
-acsl-import-addon-ensures-and-exits  adds ensures_and_exits extension clause
                    (opposite option is
                    -acsl-import-no-addon-ensures-and-exits)
-acsl-import-addon-integer-cast  elucidates implicit and explicit casts from
                    integers to C integral types (opposite option is
                    -acsl-import-no-addon-integer-cast)
-acsl-import-include-dirs <d1,...,dn>  directories for searching ACSL files
                    to include (preferably use
                    -acsl-import-include-dirs="d1,...,dn")
-acsl-import-keep-unused-symbols  keeps unused C symbols (opposite option is
                    -acsl-import-no-keep-unused-symbols)
-acsl-import-parse-only  parses the ACSL files without typing nor imports
                    (opposite option is -acsl-import-no-parse-only)
-acsl-import-run    runs the plugin (other options just configure its
                    parameters) (set by default, opposite option is
                    -acsl-import-no-run)
-acsl-import-type-only  parses and types the ACSL files without imports
                    (opposite option is -acsl-import-no-type-only)
-acsl-import-ulevel-spec <spec1,...,specs>  an unrolling specification
                    <m@f:tag@n> adds a 'loop unfold "tag", <n>;' to the loop
                    of the function <f> of occurrence <m>.
                     An unrolling specification <c@f:tag@n> adds a 'loop
                    unfold "tag", <n>;' to all loops of category <c> of the
                    function <f> where allowed loop categories are: 'while',
                    'for' and 'do-while'.
                     The specification is considered as a set of elementary
                    specifications: spec1,...,specs.
                     Categories, function names and loop occurrence numbers
                    can be omitted. The priority ordering used for choosing
                    the ("tag", unrolling value <n>) pair is: m@f:tag@n >
                    c@f:tag@n > f:tag@n > c:tag@n > :tag@n.
                     The default value for optional tags is the empty string
                    which leads to add a loop pragmas without tags.
                     Nothing is done for loops having already a clause 'loop
                    unfold ...'. (preferably use
                    -acsl-import-ulevel-spec="spec1,...,specs")
-acsl-import-unroll-loop-conditions  unrolls statements related to loop
                    conditions (opposite option is
                    -acsl-import-no-unroll-loop-conditions)

*** DEBUG

-acsl-import-debug <n>  level of debug for plug-in ACSL importer (default to
                    0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-acsl-import-help   help of plug-in ACSL importer
-acsl-import-h      alias for option -acsl-import-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-acsl-import-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from ACSL importer to a
                    file. <K> is a combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -acsl-import-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-acsl-import-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -acsl-import-msg-key help to get a
                    list of available categories, and * to enable all
                    categories (preferably use
                    -acsl-import-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-acsl-import-verbose <n>  level of verbosity for plug-in ACSL importer
                    (default to 1)
-acsl-import-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for
                    category <k1> to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use
                    -acsl-import-warn-key help to get a list of available
                    categories, and * to enable all categories. Possible
                    statuses are inactive, feedback, warning, error, abort,
                    feedback-once, warning-once, error-once. Defaults to
                    warning. (preferably use
                    -acsl-import-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
